President Obama has announced his intent to nominate Michael Khouri as a Member of the Federal Maritime Commission. Khouri has over 35 years of experience in the maritime industry and has held various positions in vessel operations, legal, and executive roles. He is currently an attorney in private practice and has previously served as President & Chief Operating Officer at MERS/Economy Boat. Khouri has also held executive positions at American Commercial Lines and began his career as a crewman on Crounse Corporation vessels. He has served on the Boards of Directors of the American Waterways Operators Association and the Waterways Council, Inc. Khouri holds a B.A. in Economics from Tulane University, a J.D. from the Brandeis School of Law-University of Louisville, and is a graduate of the Advanced Management Program at Harvard Business School.